text:
Here's some tips (Though i doubt Gura will see this) [and i havn't watched the vid of gura playing with the other vtuber in dbd yet, so maybe she found these out already]
- Default trapper can only hold one trap at a time, you need to place the trap in your hands before you can pick up a new one.
- It isn't really advised to leave a chase to kick a generator [Or leave a injured chase in general], You want to cause the survivor's as much "pressure" as possible, And getting a down/hooking them is A lot of pressure, it means one isn't doing anything (on hook) and one (or more) have to come for the rescue;
- If you do kick a gen, You need to completely hold down space; at 21:20 you can see you let go before the bar is finished, So it isn't regressing
- i'm pretty sure it's advised not to kick generators at all, as it's a "waste of time", unless you have pop or overcharge, etc (though i was only rank 12 back when i played, so not that good] But i think that's what newer killers freak out about, is like "AHH that gen, i NEED to kick it; But the 5 seconds or whatever it takes you to kick it, can be ondone with them tapping the gen, And the regress speed is pretty bad too if i recall

i know gura wasn't being tottally serious, but tips are tips, even if not serious, These could be helpful if she doesn't know

text:
10:00 introducting Dead By Daylight's newest killer...

The Idol

Name: Hoshimachi Suisei
Gender: Female
Nationality: Japanese
Realm: Project Winter
Power: Virtual Suicopathy
Weapon: Tetris "T-Block" Axe
Movement Speed: 115%/ 4.6 m/s
Terror Radius: 29 meters
Height: Average
DLC: Hollowed Live (Lead Developer: Motoagi "Yagoo" Tanigo)

The Idol is a ghost of modern Japanese internet urban legend who uses virtual reality to deceive and disorientate survivors. Virtual Suicopathy allows the Idol to impersonate survivors when out of chase, and then proceed to inflict a lunging attack with her Tetris Axe to any unsuspecting survivors who are not quick enough to react to her ambush attack's auditory warning. A successful ambush hit inflicts the deep wound effect and a decrease in speed for a few seconds, but a missed hit stuns her for a brief moment.

Her teachable perks, Hearty Meal, Hex: Obsessive Attention, and Stargazer's Watch allows her to apply pressure to all survivors both near and far.

Difficulty Rating: Intermediate

Lore:

Hoshimachi Suisei was a seemingly modest, multitalented singer and aspiring idol who was among the more level-headed members of hololive, though she also has a childish streak. After her unexpectedly compelling performance as a traitor in a game of Project Winter, she gained a reputation for remorseless sociopathy behind a facade of polite sweetness. No one seems to know how much of the "Psychopath Suisei" persona is real or not, but Suisei herself acknowledges that it is extremely funny and has referred to the incident on multiple occasions.

Over time, she would spend more and more of her time honing her reflex skills in games such as Tetris and in understanding how to entrap victims via innocuous plays in Project Winter. As time passes on, she started to stray away from the idol path she had originally wanted and sought more...."animalistic hobbies". In spite of her changing psyche, she was still capable of presenting an outward image of a sweet and lovable idol to the world with her many gifts and talents.

Eventually, this facade came to an abrupt end when one day, multiple staff members of Hololive were found dead with body parts and certain internal organs missing. All the killings occured in one fateful night inside the Cover Corp. Headquarters. Investigations concluded that the culprit was none other than Hoshimachi Suisei. Upon finding the only functioning security camera that recorded that fateful night, the investigators found a bloodied Suisei walking outside of the front entrance, only to be engulfed by an eerie fog that left no traces of her.

Now within the realm of The Entity, she gained a newfound purpose in life: to revel in her psychopathic indulgences without needing to follow the restrictive lifestyle of her previous idol life. Swearing every fibre of her being to sacrifice on The Entity's behalf in exchange for an audience of victims to which she could use to both her narcissistic merriment and for her twisted consumption of human flesh.

The Idol's Perks:

Hearty Meal: Once per trial, allows the killer to kill the obsession by their own hands if they have been hooked twice. Once a survivor has been killed, apply the dying state on another survivor to see the auras of the other survivors who are at least 42 meters away from you for 3/5/7 seconds. Any survivors outside your terror radius receives the oblivious status effect for 30 seconds.

Hex: Obsessive Attention: allows for the creation of two Hex totems on opposite ends of the map. Once one of the totems gets cleansed, blocks all unfinished generators except for the one closest to the killer for 40/60/120 seconds. This Hex can be deactivated prematurely by cleansing the remaining active Hex totem, and also heals one random survivor by one health state if applicable.

Stargazer's Watch: start the match with 5 tokens. activates when a generator being worked on by two or more survivors with at least 50% repair progress receives a failed skill check which reduces tokens by 1. This incurs a 20%/ 30%/ 35% generator regression penalty. This perk has a cool down of 80 seconds. A token is gained everytime you hit the obsession, up to a maximum of 2 additional tokens.

text:
Love in English is more generic than in pretty much every other language. It can be just as powerful but also much more casual. In other languages love doesn't have that casual aspect which is why they are more careful in it's use and most of the time they also have different levels of it. Like in spanish my native language. Te quiero and te amo are both I love you but one is much stronger in feeling and isn't used lightly in real life. Quiero is also closer to I want you or I care for you etc. From what I understand in japan it's similar on top of the fact that japanese people tend to be more reserved with those types of affection.
Edit. To help understand I'll use some more examples using my native tongue.
I love chicken
Mi gusta poyo
Both mean the same thing but notice I didn't use amo or quiero.
You could also use encanta instead of gusta to have the same effect. The point being the word love is very flexible

Hey there, if you are going to play Depth, I want you to know that divers can hear sharks dashing and sprinting from quite a distance away. Also, try not to cast your shadow onto light ground.  I recommend playing both sides to understand divers' POV to be a better shark. That, and there are usually veterans playing unless there's an event going on. Some of them are so good you might think they are cheating!
Also, when a diver's in your jaws, max mouse sensitivity doesn't help thrash divers faster, just need to have your mouse moving.
